ings</a></em>, &#8220;<strong>Here&#8217;s the hard thing about easy things=
:</strong> if everyone can do something, there&#8217;s no advantage to doin=
g it, but you still have to do it anyway just to keep up.&#8221; If the <st=
rong>protocols </strong>make it easier for developers to build <strong>appl=
ications</strong>, more people may build applications and compete away prof=
its.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26p=
x; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">New web3 primitives might spell trouble for the incu=
mbent networks, but it&#8217;s still unclear where the value accrues in thi=
